<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> impose on someone • impose oneself on someone</xh5><p> <i>impose on someone—</i>obtain a favor from a person, especially by using persuasion or undue pressure: Could I <u>impose on</u> you for a little help with this translation?</p><p> <i>impose oneself on someone—</i>inconvenience smb. by one’s presence: As there was no train, he was forced to <u>impose himself on</u> his hosts for longer than he had intended.</p> </entry>
